		  <div style="opacity:0" class="sc-faUpoM cFOwMS __pf __pf_qvED0WW5" id="__pf"><div data-pf-type="Body" class="sc-bGaVxB eYgBNP pf-1_"><div data-pf-type="Layout" class="sc-ksHpcM hkPZIR pf-2_"><div data-section-id="pf-a43e" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-gHjyzD fopdnV pf-3_"><div class="sc-JEhMO dxozkW"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-4_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-5_"><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-6_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-8_">What is CSTF Mandatory + Statutory Training?
</span></h1><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-9_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-11_">All healthcare workers must complete relevant statutory and mandatory training in line with their job roles, including the annual refresher courses.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-12_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-13_"><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-14_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-16_">Which type of mandatory training do I need?</span></p><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-17_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-19_">Healthcare organisations have legal responsibilities to ensure that their staff receives training to develop the knowledge and skills to ensure a safe and healthy workplace (Garcaz &amp; Wilcock 2005). To improve healthcare services, organisations must meet the quality standards required by the government and other agencies.<br><br>This blog will discuss CSTF statutory and mandatory training, who supports the framework and what subjects are under the guidance of the said framework.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-7ba7" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-gHjyzD fopdnV pf-20_"><div class="sc-JEhMO dxozkW"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-21_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-22_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-23_"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-24_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-25_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-26_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-28_">What is the Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF)?</span></h2><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-29_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-31_">Skills launched the UK CSTF for Health in 2013. The CSTF aims to enable consistency in the core content of statutory and mandatory education and training. The CSTF is the key enabler of portability for statutory and mandatory training across the NHS. Since October 2019, Skills for Health (SfH) and HEE have collaborated to publish and manage a CSTF for NHS Trusts in England, comprising 11 statutory and mandatory subjects.
<br><br>Since 2013, the Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF) has become a national minimum standard for statutory/mandatory training in the health sector. It is a collection of recommendations covering the key statutory and mandatory training subjects for many roles in the health sector.
<br><br>This Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF) Statutory/Mandatory Subject Guide sets out for each identified skill area an organising structure which offers:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-dcgwPl kGdrcc pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-33_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-35_">Context statement</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-36_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-38_">Current policy and legal references with hyperlinks</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-39_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-41_">Relevant target audience</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-42_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-44_">Key learning outcomes</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-45_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-47_">The required frequency of refresher training or assessment</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-48_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-50_">Standards for training delivery</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-51_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-53_">Identification of any available National Occupational Standards.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-54_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-55_"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-56_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-57_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-58_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-60_">Who supports the Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF)?</span></h2><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-61_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-63_">The following are the sectors that support the Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF):</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-dcgwPl kGdrcc pf-64_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-65_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-67_">The Independent Healthcare Advisory Services (IHAS)</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-68_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-70_">The National Association of Healthcare Fire Officers</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-71_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-73_">The Infection Prevention Society</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-74_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-76_">The Health and Safety Executive</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-77_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-79_">The National Back Exchange</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-80_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-82_">Resuscitation Council (UK).</span></li></ul><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-83_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-85_">Effective use of the CSTF should help promote consistency and quality of training, help prevent needless duplication of training, provide better direct resources for quality and risk management and help achieve efficiency benefits relevant for organisations and learners.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-86_"></div></div></div><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-87_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-88_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-89_"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-90_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-91_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-92_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-94_">Is statutory and mandatory training the same?</span></h2><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-95_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-97_">One of the challenges related to the issue of statutory and mandatory training is the interchangeable use of terms of statutory and mandatory training. For CSTF, the following definitions have been used:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-dcgwPl kGdrcc pf-98_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-99_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-101_"><b>Statutory training</b> - Training that employers are legally required to provide as defined by law and for which there is a stated legal reference and/or where a government or regulatory body have instructed employers to provide training based on legislation.
<br><br>These examples would include:</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-102_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-104_">Health and Safety training</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-105_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-107_">Equality Act 2010</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-108_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-110_">Fire safety training.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-111_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-113_"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Mandatory training </span>- This is a training requirement that organisations themselves have determined.<br><br>This can include:</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-114_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-116_"><b>The policy required mandatory training</b> - These are requirements for mandatory training that a government department has determined, or regulatory body, as part of implementing an agreed national policy.
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-117_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-119_"><b>Organisationally required mandatory training</b> - Organisations set these training requirements themselves. These requirements are usually introduced to ensure that the organisation complies with key risk areas that might impact safety.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-120_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-121_"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-122_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-123_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-124_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-126_">What subjects are under the CSTF statutory and mandatory training guidance?</span></h2><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-127_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-129_">The subjects under the CSTF statutory and mandatory training guidance are as follows:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-dcgwPl kGdrcc pf-130_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-131_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-133_">Conflict Resolution</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-134_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-136_">Equality, Diversity and Human Rights</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-137_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-139_">Fire Safety</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-140_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-142_">Health, Safety and Welfare</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-143_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-145_">Infection Prevention and Control</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-146_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-148_">Information Governance and Data Security</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-149_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-151_">Moving and Handling</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-152_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-154_">Preventing Radicalisation</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-155_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-157_">Resuscitation</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-158_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-160_">Safeguarding Adults</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-161_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-163_">Safeguarding Children.</span></li></ul><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-164_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-166_">CSTF alignment requires the learning outcomes for each CSTF subject to be met. The framework does not prescribe training methods - however, some subjects will require a practical training component.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-167_"></div></div></div><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-168_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-169_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-170_"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-171_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-172_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-173_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-175_">What are the organisational benefits of the CSTF guidance?</span></h2><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-176_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-178_">The key benefits of the CSTF are:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-dcgwPl kGdrcc pf-179_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-180_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-182_">It provides consolidation and integration of available guidance that organisations can use to inform and rationalise the delivery of statutory and mandatory training activity.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-183_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-185_">It provides a guide for those who have accountability for corporate governance, is responsible for the delivery of training activity, and internal advisors to have a joint statement that they can use to audit and determine how the organisation can best meet or exceed the guidance offered here.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-186_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-188_">It helps organisations guide training delivery quality and consistency for the identified subjects.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-189_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-191_">It helps set more explicit expected staff performance levels following any core skills training delivery.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-192_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-194_">It can guide some of the measures that might be used to assess the effectiveness and impact of the supported training activity.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-ehIJor kvifwM pf-195_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-197_">It can guide the development of a specification for organisations that might need/or wish to commission external training providers to deliver any core skills training.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9e78" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-gHjyzD fopdnV pf-198_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-JEhMO dxozkW"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-199_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-200_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-201_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-203_">Upcoming CSTF Webinars</span></h2><p class="sc-iukxot iZqxsD pf-204_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-206_">We have ‘<span style="font-weight: bold;">CSTF STATUTORY &amp; MANDATORY TRAINING</span>' courses available online.</span></p><a href="/collections/online-mandatory-training-courses-cstf-mandatory-elearning-courses" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-fyrocj bsLbEw pf-207_ animate-grow-shadow"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-209_">Click here to register for this CSTF course</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-f93e" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-gHjyzD fopdnV pf-210_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-JEhMO dxozkW"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-211_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fydGpi bMfPUC pf-212_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edERGn cHFtyQ pf-213_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hgKiOD hnskCB pf-215_">Other Recommended Statutory and Mandatory Training Courses</span></h2>